wfMplsAtmIfConfTable.name: wfMplsAtmIfConfTable
wfMplsAtmIfConfTable.description: MPLS ATM interface configuration table - This tabulates the ATM interfaces within an mpls protocol group. All interfaces are indexed according to their line number. There is one ATM interface per MPLS LDP session, but there might be more LDP sessions per ATM interface.

wfMplsAtmIfCreate.name: wfMplsAtmIfCreate
wfMplsAtmIfCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users modify this object in order to create/delete MPLS ATM interfaces

wfMplsAtmIfConfLineNumber.name: wfMplsAtmIfConfLineNumber
wfMplsAtmIfConfLineNumber.description: The line number of the driver line to which the interface belongs.

wfMplsAtmIfDebugLogMask.name: wfMplsAtmIfDebugLogMask
wfMplsAtmIfDebugLogMask.description: Log bits for debug messages. This values above can be used separately, or OR'd together for a combination of debug levels.

wfMplsAtmIfStatusTable.name: wfMplsAtmIfStatusTable
wfMplsAtmIfStatusTable.description: MPLS ATM interface status table - This tabulates the ATM interfaces within an mpls protocol group. All interfaces are indexed according to their line number. There is one ATM interface per MPLS LDP session, but there might be multiple LDP sessions per ATM interface.

wfMplsAtmIfOperStatus.name: wfMplsAtmIfOperStatus
wfMplsAtmIfOperStatus.description: The current state of the MPLS ATM interface

wfMplsAtmIfStatusLineNumber.name: wfMplsAtmIfStatusLineNumber
wfMplsAtmIfStatusLineNumber.description: The line number of the driver line to which the interface belongs.

wfMplsAtmIfCircuit.name: wfMplsAtmIfCircuit
wfMplsAtmIfCircuit.description: The circuit number of the circuit to which the interface belongs.

wfMplsAtmIfTotalSess.name: wfMplsAtmIfTotalSess
wfMplsAtmIfTotalSess.description: The total number of LDPs up running.

wfMplsAtmIfTotalVcs.name: wfMplsAtmIfTotalVcs
wfMplsAtmIfTotalVcs.description: The total number of VCs either in use, or available on this interface.

wfMplsAtmIfAllocVcs.name: wfMplsAtmIfAllocVcs
wfMplsAtmIfAllocVcs.description: The number of VCs which are currently allocated for different LDP sessions on this interface. wfMplsAtmTotalVcs minus the value of this object results in knowning how many VCs are still available to allocate to new LDP sessions on this interface.

wfMplsAtmSessConfTable.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfTable
wfMplsAtmSessConfTable.description: This is the ATM related configuration table for every LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessAdminStatus.name: wfMplsAtmSessAdminStatus
wfMplsAtmSessAdminStatus.description: Specifies the desired administrative state of the VCL. The up and down states indicate that the traffic flow is enabled and disabled respectively for the VCL.

wfMplsAtmSessConfLineNumber.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfLineNumber
wfMplsAtmSessConfLineNumber.description: Uniquely identifies the interface (port) that contains the appropriate management information. We use line number here.

wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVpi.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVpi
wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVpi.description: The VPI value of the default VC.

wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVci
wfMplsAtmSessConfDefVclVci.description: The VCI value of the default VC. It should not in the configured VC range for any LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeVpi.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeVpi
wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeVpi.description: The VPI value of the VCs in this LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMinVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMinVci
wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMinVci.description: The minimum VCI value of the configured LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMaxVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMaxVci
wfMplsAtmSessConfVcRangeMaxVci.description: The maximum VCI value of the configured LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtPeakCellRate.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtPeakCellRate
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtPeakCellRate.description: Transmit (Forward) Peak Cell Rate in cells/second. This specifies the upper bound on the traffic that can be submitted on an ATM connection. 0 means best effort peak cell rate.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtSustainableCellRat.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtSustainableCellRate
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtSustainableCellRat.description: Transmit (Forward) Sustainable Cell Rate in cells/second. This specifies the upper bound on the conforming average rate of an ATM connection, where 'average rate' is the number of cells transmitted divided by the 'duration of the connection'. 0 means best effort sustainable cell rate.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtQosClass.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtQosClass
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtQosClass.description: Transmit (Forward) Quality of Service as specified in Appendix A, Section 4 of the ATM Forum UNI Specification, Version 3.0

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvPeakCellRate.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvPeakCellRate
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvPeakCellRate.description: Receive (Backward) Peak Cell Rate in cells/second. This specifies the upper bound on the traffic that can be submitted on an ATM connection. 0 means best effort peak cell rate.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvSustainableCellRat.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvSustainableCellRate
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvSustainableCellRat.description: Receive (Backward) Sustainable Cell Rate in cells/second. This specifies the upper bound on the conforming average rate of an ATM connection, where 'average rate' is the number of cells transmitted divided by the 'duration of the connection'. 0 means best effort sustainable cell rate.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvQosClass.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvQosClass
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvQosClass.description: Receive (Backward) Quality of Service as specified in Appendix A, Section 4 of the ATM Forum UNI Specification, Version 3.0

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalType.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalType
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalType.description: The type of AAL used on the VCL.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsTransmitSduSiz.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsTransmitSduSize
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsTransmitSduSiz.description: The maximum AAL CPCS SDU size in octets that is supported on the transmit direction of this VCC.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsReceiveSduSize.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsReceiveSduSize
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalCpcsReceiveSduSize.description: The maximum AAL CPCS SDU size in octets that is supported on the receive direction of this VCC.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalEncapsType.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalEncapsType
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclAalEncapsType.description: The type of data encapsulation used over both AAL3/4 and AAL5 SSCS layer. Currently, the only values supported are : ATM_VCLENCAPS_LLCENCAPS - RFC1483 ATM_VCLENCAPS_ROUTEDPROTO - NONE

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCongestionIndication.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCongestionIndication
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCongestionIndication.description: The desired state of the Congestion Indication (CI) bit in the payload field of each ATM cell for this VCL.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCellLossPriority.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCellLossPriority
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclCellLossPriority.description: The desired state of the Cell Loss Priority (CLP) bit in the ATM header of each cell for this VCL.

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtTagging.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtTagging
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclXmtTagging.description: Tagging forward VC messages if peak/sustainable rates exceeded

wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvTagging.name: wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvTagging
wfMplsAtmSessDefVclRcvTagging.description: Tagging backward VC messages if peak/sustainable rates exceeded

wfMplsAtmSessStatusTable.name: wfMplsAtmSessStatusTable
wfMplsAtmSessStatusTable.description: This is the ATM related status table for every LDP session.

wfMplsAtmSessOperStatus.name: wfMplsAtmSessOperStatus
wfMplsAtmSessOperStatus.description: The ATM related LDP session state.

wfMplsAtmSessStatusLineNumber.name: wfMplsAtmSessStatusLineNumber
wfMplsAtmSessStatusLineNumber.description: Uniquely identifies the interface (port) that contains the appropriate management information. We use line number here.

wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeVpi.name: wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeVpi
wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeVpi.description: The VPI value of the actually allowable VC range for this session. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVpiBits.

wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMinVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMinVci
wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMinVci.description: The minimum VCI value of the actually allowable VC range for LDP session. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits.

wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMaxVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMaxVci
wfMplsAtmSessActualVcRangeMaxVci.description: The maximum VCI value of the actually allowable VC range for LDP session. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits.

wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeVpi.name: wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeVpi
wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeVpi.description: The VPI value of the VCs negotiated with LDP peer for this LDP session. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVpiBits. -1 means it is not possible.

wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMinVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMinVci
wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMinVci.description: The minimum VCI value of VCs negotiated with LDP peer for this LDP session. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits.

wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMaxVci.name: wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMaxVci
wfMplsAtmSessNegotiatedVcRangeMaxVci.description: The maximum VCI value of VCs negotiated with LDP peer for this LDP session. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits.

wfMplsAtmSessInboundInuseVcs.name: wfMplsAtmSessInboundInuseVcs
wfMplsAtmSessInboundInuseVcs.description: number of VCs opened for inbound LSP.

wfMplsAtmSessOutboundInuseVcs.name: wfMplsAtmSessOutboundInuseVcs
wfMplsAtmSessOutboundInuseVcs.description: number of VCs opened for outbound LSP.

wfMplsAtmVclLineNumber.name: wfMplsAtmVclLineNumber
wfMplsAtmVclLineNumber.description: Uniquely identifies the interface (port) that contains the appropriate management information. We use line number here.

wfMplsAtmVclVpi.name: wfMplsAtmVclVpi
wfMplsAtmVclVpi.description: The VPI value of the VCL. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfMplsAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVpiBits.

wfMplsAtmVclVci.name: wfMplsAtmVclVci
wfMplsAtmVclVci.description: The VCI value of the VCL. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by the wfMplsAtmInterfaceMaxActiveVciBits.

wfMplsAtmVclLdpIndex.name: wfMplsAtmVclLdpIndex
wfMplsAtmVclLdpIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the LDP session number in this interface.

wfMplsAtmVclType.description: default VC or normal LSP VC.
